---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Neuroethics Foundations — Qinnovate"
  description="Core philosophy and the human-centric mission of securing brain-computer interfaces."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Governance', href: '/governance/' }, { label: 'Foundations' }]}
>
  <div class="prose max-w-none">
    <h1>Neuroethics Foundations</h1>
    
    <p class="lead">
      The technical problems in BCI security are real, but the harder problems are human. 
      Who decides what a neural device is allowed to do? What does informed consent look like when the technology interfaces with cognition itself?
    </p>

    <h2>Why Neuroethics?</h2>
    <p>
      BCI security is not just an engineering problem; it is a patient rights problem. 
      Every proposed neurorights framework—cognitive liberty, mental privacy, psychological continuity—can be violated through technical pathways that already exist. 
      The question is whether we build governance before the harm, or after.
    </p>

    <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6 my-8 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">
      <h3 class="!mt-0 text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">The Principles-to-Protocol Gap</h3>
      <p class="mb-0">
        There is a significant gap between high-level ethical principles and the low-level protocols that govern neural data. 
        QIF aims to bridge this gap by operationalizing neurorights into technical specifications.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>The Human Lens</h2>
    <p>
      My background is in cybersecurity. I understand layered defense, threat modeling, and vulnerability analysis. 
      But what drew me to neuroethics is the recognition that the most important safeguards for brain-computer interfaces will not be technical. 
      They will be the policies, consent frameworks, and ethical guidelines that determine how these technologies are developed, tested, and deployed.
    </p>

    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-12 not-prose">
      <a href="/governance/rights/" class="glass p-6 rounded-xl hover:bg-white/5 transition-colors group">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2 group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] transition-colors">Mental Integrity</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">How we distinguish between "unaltered" and "self-originating" signals.</p>
        <div class="mt-4 text-xs font-medium text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">Read about Neurorights &rarr;</div>
      </a>
      <a href="/atlas/tara/" class="glass p-6 rounded-xl hover:bg-white/5 transition-colors group">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2 group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)] transition-colors">Threat Atlas</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">109 catalogued techniques mapped to clinical outcomes.</p>
        <div class="mt-4 text-xs font-medium text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)]">Explore the Atlas &rarr;</div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
